# Authentik OAuth2/OIDC provider setup for Backplane public MCP
#
# In Authentik admin UI:
# 1. Applications -> Providers -> Create -> OAuth2/OpenID Provider
#    - Name: Backplane MCP
#    - Client type: Confidential
#    - Authorization flow: default (or your preferred user login flow)
#    - Redirect URIs (upstream OAuth app — single fixed callback):
#      https://backplane-mcp.worgarsi.de/auth/callback
#      ChatGPT uses separate dynamic redirect URIs validated by Backplane DCR.
#    - Scopes (Applications -> Providers -> Backplane MCP -> edit -> Scopes):
#      openid (required) and offline_access (required for ChatGPT custom connectors).
#      Without offline_access, Backplane's upstream /token has no refresh_token and
#      ChatGPT often fails after OAuth with "There was a problem connecting …".
#      Optional: profile, email. Do not add mcp.read or mcp.write until MCP-facing
#      scope mapping is verified.
#      If offline_access is missing from the picker: Customization -> Scopes, then
#      add it on the provider.
# 2. Applications -> Applications -> Create
#    - Link to the provider above
#    - Slug: backplane-mcp (avoid reserved slugs: authorize, token, userinfo, ...)
# 3. Restrict access with an application policy / group binding
#
# Copy the values below into the Backplane host .env (see .env.example).

MCP_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://backplane-mcp.worgarsi.de
MCP_OIDC_CONFIG_URL=https://auth.worgarsi.de/application/o/backplane-mcp/.well-known/openid-configuration
MCP_OIDC_CLIENT_ID=
MCP_OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=
